entry.content:
Whenever a new seat capability event is received always bind to a new

input (pointer/touch/keyboard) device.

This will ensure that if for some reason a remove capability event is

missed in between two capability added events for the same device type a

stale device is no longer bound.



This is aimed to address a corner case scenario due to possible

differences in compositors before version 5 vs. compositors from version

5 onwards in terms of handling of previously bound devices as specified

in the spec.

entry.title: Deflake BFCache test
entry.content:
BackForwardCacheStillLoadingBrowserTest.DoesNotCacheIfFrameStillLoading

is flaky on MSan, and fails more consistently when changing navigation

timing (BlinkSchedulerPrioritizeNavigationIPCs feature).



The failures occur when Unload doesn't have a chance to run in the

initial a.com/controlled renderer. When this happens, the a.com cache

entry doesn't get finalized (as a failure), and the subsequent a.com

request is served out of the memory cache instead of resulting in a

404 from the embedded test server -- which is what the test is

expecting.



To fix this, this CL adds a call to DisableUnloadTimerForTesting() on

a.com's render frame host.

entry.title: Plumb BoxBackgroundPaintContext not BackgroundImageGeometry
entry.content:
This CL changes instantiations of BackgroundImageGeometry objects into

instantiations of BoxBackgroundPaintContext, while making the later no

longer be a part of the former. BoxPainterBase::PaintFillLayer() now

creates one BackgroundImageGeometry per-layer, only keeping it alive

within said function. This separates per-layer state from per-entity

(usually box/fragment) state.



Most of the changes in this CL only removes the indirection via the

BackgroundImageGeometry object or changes access from a field to a

passed in parameter.



Since the BoxBackgroundPaintContext now provides the means to read

geometric information about the box, the same functionality on

BoxPainterBase (ComputeBorders/ComputePadding) can be removed.



This will allow reusing the majority of BackgroundImageGeometry for

SVGMaskPainter in a future CL.

entry.title: vt: Fix CHECK trying to merge anonymous block
entry.content:
This CHECK would trip as changing listStylePosition triggers a layout

tree reattachment[1]. This causes the documentElement's LayoutObject to

be removed which happens before the LayoutViewTransitionRoot.



LayoutViewTransitionRoot represents the snapshot containing block and

doesn't have an associated Node, making it "anonymous".



When documentElement's object is removed, it removes itself from the

parent LayoutView. Since LayoutViewTransitionRoot is the only remaining

child, LayoutView tries to hoist its contents onto itself in

CollapseAnonymousBlockChild[2] since anonymous blocks are typically

created artificially to host non-block content in a block flow. This

tries to add the ::view-transition LayoutObject to LayoutView which

trips the CHECK that LayoutView doesn't yet have a

LayoutViewTransitionRoot, since doing so will add one.



LayoutViewTransitionRoot is anonymous but doesn't want to have this

merging/collapsing property so this CL opts it out of that behavior.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/style/computed_style.cc;l=372;drc=a9187270cee16e9adf8ba3b0286ab80694448a70

[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_block_flow.cc;l=271;drc=0e6e802410c16813e03bd2884f8e7f7889b87783

entry.title: Refactor: Delete VideoFrameBufferPreparer helper class.
entry.content:
This CL replaces the frame preparer class with a smaller, simpler

struct VideoFrameInitData. This CL does not change any of the code

needed to prepare the media::VideoFrame from the ReadyBufferPtr, it only

refactors and moves it with the following goals:

1. Reduce risk of use-after-free (example: [1]) by removing raw ptrs to

VideoCaptureImpl.

2. Inline some code that was previously spread out in the file.

3. Make it more clear that before OnVideoFrameReady(), the buffer can

EITHER be a media::VideoFrame OR a gfx::GpuMemoryBuffer, and only in

the latter case do we need a round-trip to the media task runner.



This is achieved as follows:

- VideoFrameInitData uses absl::variant<> for "frame_or_buffer".

- VideoFrameBufferPreparer::Initialize() is replaced by

CreateVideoFrameInitData().

- VideoFrameBufferPreparer::BindVideoFrameOnMediaThread() is changed

into a static function without any raw ptr to VideoCaptureImpl.

- The VideoFrameBufferPreparer::Finalize() and

VideoCaptureImpl::BindVideoFrameOnMediaTaskRunner() steps are inlined.



[1] UAF example: https://crbug.com/1511200

entry.title: [ChromeSigninBubble] Simplify the avatar button logic when the bubble is shown
entry.content:
Want to achieve:

Disable the avatar button action while the chrome signin bubble is shown

but keep the button in an active state from the UI perspective, so

that the button seems active (for the bubble) but not doing it's

initial purpose (showing the profile menu).



Following up on https://crrev.com/c/5038754: this CL introduced a

complex logic where the button would be disabled but trying to

override the active UI properties.

It appeared later while testing that the solution was not complete,

and some cases with different darker themes would break the text

visibility.



This CL removes the previous mentioned logic, and implement a

way simpler one: simply bypass the button action while the

bubble is shown. This way the state of the button is not affected

directly so the UI is not as well, only the effect of clicking the

button is ignored while the bubble is shown.

entry.title: [PM] Set the priority of spare ProcessNodeImpls to low
entry.content:
Before this CL, a process would always be assigned a high priority

until the first execution context (frame or worker) would be

added to that process and determine its correct priority.



This doesn't work for spare processes, since they are designed to

stay up for long period of times without hosting an execution

context.



With this change, a spare renderer will be backgrounded soon after

initialization, and remain this way until it hosts its first frame

or worker.

entry.title: WebNN: Decouple command list recording from execution for DirectML
entry.content:
This CL mainly decouples the command list recording from execution

to optimize the graph execution performance for DirectML backend.



After refactoring the `dml::CommandRecorder` and `dml::GraphImpl`,

some detailed changes are:



1. `dml::CommandRecorder::Close()` and

`dml::CommandRecorder::Execute()` methods are added to decouple the

command list closing from execution.



2. `dml::GraphImpl::RecordGraphExecution()` method mainly records

the graph execution onto the command list, binds all required

resources and closes the command list.



The method is called firstly after the graph initialization has been

completed to prepare for the first graph execution. For following

graph executions, the method only needs to be called if we need to

record commands and bind resources again.



3. `dml::GraphImpl::ComputeImpl()` calls

`dml::CommandRecorder::Execute()` that submits the command list for

execution and references all required resources.



4. `dml::GraphImpl::PersistentResource` struct is introduced to

encapsulate the persistent buffer, its binding and description.

`dml::GraphImpl::OnCompilationComplete()` allocates it and pass it

along the way to the `dml::GraphImpl`.



Based on these changes, the most important benefit is that it avoids

re-calling the `IDMLCommandRecorder::RecordDispatch` and

`ID3D12GraphicsCommandList::Close` methods which may be time-consuming

for some devices during the first execution and following executions

of a graph if not needed.



Bug: 1273291

entry.title: Change the route of passing is_ad_resource flag
entry.content:
The renderer process's PageTimingMetricsSender accumulates resource data

usage information as PageResourceDataUse structure and sends it in

batches to the browser process.



The PageResourceDataUse structure contains the data usage information

(total_received_bytes_, encoded_body_length_, decoded_body_length_) and

the `reported_as_ad_resource_` flag. These data is used to measure the

data usage for ads.



Currently the data usage information and the ads flag are passed through

different route. This CL unifies them.



[1] For subresources:

The data usage information is passed from ResourceRequestSender:

ResourceRequestSender

->ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper

->WeakWrapperResourceLoadInfoNotifier

->RenderFrameImpl

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver

->PageTimingMetricsSender

->PageResourceDataUse



The ads flags is passed from ResourceLoader:

ResourceLoader::DidReceiveResponse()

->ResourceLoadObserverForFrame::DidReceiveResponse()

->SubresourceFilter::ReportAdRequestId()

->WebDocumentSubresourceFilterImpl::ReportAdRequestId()

->AdResourceTracker::NotifyAdResourceObserved()

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver::OnAdResourceObserved()



This route of the flag was introduced by https://crrev.com/c/1165823 at

2018 when ResourceRequestSender couldn't know the flag.

But https://crrev.com/c/4983468 introduced `is_ad_tagged` flag in

network::ResourceRequest. So now ResourceRequestSender can sends

it to the PageResourceDataUse through the route for the data usage.



[2] For navigation resources:

The data usage information is passed from NavigationBodyLoader:

NavigationBodyLoader

->ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper

->WeakWrapperResourceLoadInfoNotifier

->RenderFrameImpl

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver

->PageTimingMetricsSender

->PageResourceDataUse



The ads flags is passed from DocumentLoader:

DocumentLoader::SetSubresourceFilter()

->SubresourceFilter::SubresourceFilter()

->SubresourceFilter::ReportAdRequestId()

->WebDocumentSubresourceFilterImpl::ReportAdRequestId()

->AdResourceTracker::NotifyAdResourceObserved()

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver::OnAdResourceObserved()



This CL changes the route for the ads flag to pass the flag from

RenderFrameImpl through ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper:



RenderFrameImpl::CommitNavigation()

->WebNavigationBodyLoader::FillNavigationParamsResponseAndBodyLoader()

->ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper::NotifyResourceLoadInitiated()

->WeakWrapperResourceLoadInfoNotifier

->RenderFrameImpl

->MetricsRenderFrameObserver

->PageTimingMetricsSender

->PageResourceDataUse

entry.title: Pass PendingRemote<CodeCacheHost> for background on CommitNavigation
entry.content:
Currently one pending_remote is passed on

the CommitNavigation IPC (https://crrev.com/3033191). It is used only

for normal resource fetch from the main thread. When loading a resource

from the background thread, LoaderFactoryForFrame::

GetBackgroundCodeCacheHost() gets a new pending_remote of

blink.mojom.CodeCacheHost from BrowserInterfaceBroker. This is not good

for performance, because it can be blocked if the browser main thread

is busy.



This CL solves this problem by sending two pending_remotes of

CodeCacheHost on the CommitNavigation IPC, for the normal

resource fetch from the main thread and for the resource fetch from the

background thread.

https://crrev.com/c/5098605

builders.

As a workaround, this CL adds `siso_enabled=True` to orchestrators, too.
